items.title: Consumer sentiment nears lowest level ever as worries build over shutdown
items.description: A University of Michigan sentiment survey showed a decline of 6.2% on the month and about 30% from a year ago.

items.title: Chicago Fed's Goolsbee says he's cautious about further rate cuts during shutdown
items.description: The central bank official said told CNBC that he has concerns because of the lack of inflation reports.

items.title: 'We're past peak-restrictiveness,' BOE governor says, as bets rise on Christmas rate cut
items.description: The central bank was seen as more likely to hold rates than not, according to economists.

items.title: Job cuts in October hit highest level for the month in 22 years, Challenger says
items.description: Job cuts for October totaled 153,074, a 183% surge from September.

items.title: Op-ed: The fuel for the AI boom driving the markets is advertising. It is also an existential risk.
